The Quest game is a multiple player real time MUD.

Players can choose one of the following character types:  Cleric, Wizard, Druid, Fighter, Barbarian

Main components:
- Quests
  - you are given a sequence of quests that you must complete
- Magic System
- Object system 
- Large world map
  - move with arrow keys (n, s, e, w)
  - terrain types
  - towns and cities
  - rectangular regions that are named on the map (forsts, swamps, deserts, etc)
  - stores
  - alchemists that move around
  - caves (with a different movement)
- Combat system (fight, run away, cast, bargain (?)) 
- Hit Points / Experience points
  - If hit points goes to zero, you die
  - As experience points goes up, you go up in levels, which increases your hit points
- Castle system
  - there are many castles in the map.
  - you can buy a catapult in a store and seige a castle.
  - knights will come out to protect it, if you successfully seige
    the castle, you can take control of it.
- Viewport
  - you have a small viewport that you see the world through
  - weather impacts how much you can see
  

  
